eart muscle","Skeletal muscle tissue"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eepithelial lining of the bronchi\u003C/strong\u003E is derived from the endoderm, which forms the inner lining of the respiratory and digestive tracts and gives rise to associated organs like the liver, pancreas, and thyroid gland.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options are derived from mesoderm:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDermis of the skin\u003C/strong\u003E is of mesodermal origin\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBone tissue\u003C/strong\u003E develops from mesenchymal cells\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHeart muscle\u003C/strong\u003E develops from splanchnic mesoderm\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESkeletal muscle tissue\u003C/strong\u003E develops from somites\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe endoderm forms during gastrulation as the innermost germ layer and gives rise to the epithelial lining of the respiratory system, digestive tract, and various endocrine and exocrine organs.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The endoderm gives rise to the epithelial lining of the respiratory and digestive tracts and associated organs.","The endoderm is the innermost germ layer formed during gastrulation.","Endodermal derivatives include the liver, pancreas, thyroid, and thymus."],"references":["Sadler TW. Langman\u0027s Medical Embryology: Wolters Kluwer; 2015."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"48379"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15861"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"48379","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/48379"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-19T12:05:14+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-19T12:05:56+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8552"}},"c